{2010240003|XXGlegend|5|0|9|0|{@{}@1. Look at the record formats on the in and out ports of the Rollup. The Rollup 
component is using automatic type conversion to convert the customer_id
field from decimal(10) to integer(4).

2. Run this graph. It will fail with a "join key field type mismatch" error.
Inspect the data types of the customer_id and cust_id fields. We would like
to use integer(4) as the data type for the key field for both data sources.

3. Add a Reformat component for the "Customers, tab-delimited" data source.
Consider whether to place the Reformat component before the "Sort \{cust_id\}
component or after it.  Which design is correct?  [Answer: Reformat before Sort
is correct because changing the data type may change the way the data is
sorted. This will also get better performance because the Reformat is dropping 
fields that are not used by the Join, and because it is converting the key field to 
a data type that will require less memory during the sorting.]

4. Create a transform and output record format for the Reformat component that:
    -- converts the cust_id field to an integer(4)
    -- includes only the fields required by the Join component
       (Hint: Copy the fields from the record format on the out port of the Join.)

5. Run the graph again. What is the last name of the customer who made the
earliest purchase? [Answer: CHASE]|67000|346000|87000|366000|747000|552000|1050|}}
